en_791743_0	The Supreme Court has declared that the environmental damage caused by the thermal powerplant in Chunnakam, Jaffna, has violated the fundamental rights of the residents of the area.
en_791743_1	Accordingly, the court ordered the Northern Power Company Ltd., which operates the power plant, to pay an amount of 20 million rupees for the affected people in compensation.
en_791743_2	The Bench passing the verdict comprised of Justices Priyantha Jayawardena, Prasanna Jayawardena, and L. T. B. Dehideniya.
en_791743_3	The Court ordered that the 20 million rupees should be paid off to affected homes.
en_791743_4	The Supreme Court further noted that, only after complying with the accepted environmental conditions, the company will be allowed to operate the power plant again.
en_791743_5	Orders were given to pay the compensation within three months.
